cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper discusses a modular approach to learning in arcade-game environments, utilizing regression, supervised learning, and reinforcement learning algorithms. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it proposes a new approach to learning in complex environments. It also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with arcade-game environments as sets of interacting objects. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new approach to learning in complex environments. Finally, it involves systems and control (cs.SY) as it deals with the control of controllable objects in the environment.
